<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002034/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """It is a very practical course where the competences and skills will be acquiered and assesed progressively during the course.
In case the course is not passed progressively, students will have an exam of only those parts they have not passed during the course.
To pass the course, students must have at least a 5 out of 10.
The course is divided in two independent parts that can be lectured in any order:
- 3D design, optimization and Monte-Carlo (Fernando Barrio)
- Signal processing with Matlab (Cristina Montalvo)
Either the course begins with 3D design or with Signal processing with Matlab. This will depend on the schedule of the professors.

El carácter de la asignatura es eminentemente práctico por lo que las habilidades y competencias se irán adquiriendo y evaluando a lo largo del curso de forma continua.
En caso de no superarse la asignatura por continua, los estudiantes tendrán la oportunidad de evaluarse en la convocatoria ordinaria y extraordinaria de aquellas partes de la asignatura que no hayan superado, conservando la nota de aquellas partes que sí hayan superado.
Para superar la asignatura, los estudiantes deben obtener una nota media de 5 sobre 10 sumando todos los ítems de evaluación."""@es ;
